subject: p10933609
Findings: Comparison is made with prior studies performed earlier the same day. NG tube tip is at the level of the hemidiaphragm and should be advanced for more standard position. This finding was discussed by phone on at 3:30 pm. With. ET tube tip is 65 cm above the carina. Left IJ catheter tip is in the lower SVC. There is no pneumothorax or pleural effusion. Large bibasilar consolidations and opacities in the upper lobes bilaterally are better seen in prior CT performed the same day earlier in the morning.
